name: Aetna
summary: Several healthcare providers and insurance companies have recently been involved in contract negotiations that have impacted patient access to services. In Oregon, about 9,000 patients have been affected by the expiration of the contract between Aetna and Providence. Similarly, in Ohio, Mount Carmel and Aetna have reached a multi-year agreement to ensure patient access. Meanwhile, Aetna has filed a lawsuit against a radiology group for alleged fraudulent billing and abuse of federal arbitration. In Iowa, MercyOne and Aetna have ended a contract dispute, postponing out-of-network costs for patients. In upstate New York, Aetna and St. Joseph's Health have reached an agreement to preserve in-network coverage for many patients, while Aetna and Trinity Health have also reached a long-term agreement. Furthermore, Genesis MercyOne and Aetna have come to an understanding on a new contract, and WakeMed and Aetna are currently renegotiating their deals, with some plans being out-of-network during the transition.

name: FCC net neutrality rules
summary: A federal appeals court has struck down the Federal Communications Commission's (FCC) net neutrality rules, which aimed to regulate the internet as a public utility. This decision reverses the Biden administration's effort to restore net neutrality and is a setback for consumer advocates who argue that it is essential to protect free and open access to the internet. The court ruled that the FCC lacked the authority to regulate internet service providers (ISPs) as public utilities, and held that the previous net neutrality rules were unlawful. This ruling has been met with concern from consumer groups and Democratic lawmakers, who contend that it will allow ISPs to engage in discriminatory practices, such as blocking or slowing down access to certain websites. The court's decision is likely to be appealed, and the future of net neutrality remains uncertain.

name: Cybertruck explosion
summary: On November 22nd, 2023, an explosion outside the Trump Hotel in Las Vegas resulted in one fatality. The victim, later identified as an Army member on leave, had a self-inflicted gunshot wound to the head. Inside the exploded Cybertruck, authorities found firework mortars and gas cannisters. Officials believe the explosion was intentional and are investigating a possible link to a recent attack in New Orleans. The driver of the Cybertruck is believed to have been from Colorado Springs. Law enforcement is also considering the possibility of a terrorist motive. The explosion is still being investigated, and no arrests have been made.

name: Texas Longhorns
summary: Texas Longhorns' dramatic victory over Arizona State in the Peach Bowl has sent shockwaves through the college football world. The Longhorns almost succumbed to a late collapse but managed to prevail in overtime (45-48). Despite leading by 18 points in the fourth quarter, Texas allowed Arizona State to score twice, forcing the game into extra time. The game-winning touchdown was secured by Bijan Robinson, while Texas' defense sealed the win with an interception. This hard-fought victory marks Texas' advancement to the Cotton Bowl, with the exact time, date, and ticket information yet to be announced. Social media erupted with reactions from celebrities such as JJ Watt and Ja Morant, praising the Longhorns' resilience. For those who missed the thrilling game, a comprehensive score-by-score recap is available in the Austin American-Statesman.

summary: Jocelyn Wildenstein, the socialite known for her extensive cosmetic surgery, has passed away at the age of 84.
